  "prompt": "Who sings a song titled \"You\"?",
  "response": "Several artists across different genres have released songs titled \"You.\" Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **Chris Young**  \n   - *Genre:* Country  \n   - *Release Year:* 2015  \n   - *Details:* This song is one of Chris Young's popular tracks, showcasing his signature country sound.\n\n2. **Lana Del Rey**  \n   - *Genre:* Indie Pop/Baroque Pop  \n   - *Release Year:* 2017  \n   - *Details:* Featured on her album *Lust for Life*, this song highlights Lana Del Rey's melancholic and atmospheric style.\n\n3. **Miley Cyrus**  \n   - *Genre:* Pop  \n   - *Release Year:* 2006  \n   - *Details:* One of her earlier hits, \"You\" was part of Miley Cyrus's transition from her Hannah Montana persona to a standalone artist.\n\n4. **Yolanda Adams**  \n   - *Genre:* Gospel  \n   - *Release Year:* 1998  \n   - *Details:* A soulful and uplifting track that showcases Yolanda Adams's powerful vocal abilities.\n\n5. **Bazzi**  \n   - *Genre:* Pop/R&B  \n   - *Release Year:* 2020  \n   - *Details:* A contemporary pop song with R&B influences, reflecting Bazzi's smooth vocal style.\n\n6. **LP (Laura Pergolizzi)**  \n   - *Genre:* Indie Rock/Pop  \n   - *Release Year:* 2016  \n   - *Details:* Known for her unique voice, LP's \"You\" blends indie rock elements with heartfelt lyrics.\n\n7. **NF**  \n   - *Genre:* Hip-Hop/Rap  \n   - *Release Year:* 2021  \n   - *Details:* A deeply personal and introspective track that delves into themes of self-reflection and emotional struggle.\n\nIt's also worth noting that many other artists may have songs titled \"You,\" so if you're looking for a specific version, providing additional details like the genre, release year, or artist's name can help narrow down the search.",
